  "contentHtml": "\n                                    \n                                                                                    <ul>\n                                                                                                                                                    <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                                                                            </ul>\n                                                                                <ul>\n                                                                                            <li>Published On May 23, 2026 at 07:17 AM IST</li>\n                                                                                                                                </ul>\n                                    \n                                \n\n                    <!-- Display video article in news article for the custom next story -->\n                    \n                    <!-- Modifying the body placing embeds,promoslots,related etc.-->\n                                        <figure><img src=\"/images/default.jpg\" alt=\"\"></figure><p><a href=\"/tag/chennai\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Chennai</a>: Former WHO chief scientist <a href=\"/tag/dr+soumya+swaminathan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Dr Soumya Swaminathan</a>, who heads <a href=\"/tag/ms+swaminathan+research+foundation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">MS Swaminathan Research Foundation</a>, has been elected a Fellow of the Royal Society (FRS).The honour, among the highest a scientist can receive globally, makes Dr Soumya is the second Indian woman to be inducted into the society, after Dr Gagandeep Kang, was the first to receive the honour in 2019. Dr Soumya was director of the <a href=\"/tag/national+institute+of+tuberculosis+research\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">National Institute of Tuberculosis research</a> in Chennai, and went on to be the director general of ICMR and later chief scientist at WHO.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M --><p>She shaped scientific responses to HIV, TB, and the <a href=\"/tag/covid-19+pandemic\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Covid-19 pandemic</a>. earning her a reputation as one of the world’s most consequential and trusted public health scientists. The Royal Society recognised her pioneering research in <a href=\"/tag/paediatric+tuberculosis\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">paediatric tuberculosis</a>, her role in establishing clinical translational medicine training programmes in India, and her work in vaccine development and immunisation policy.</p><!-- PROMOSLOT_M -->\n                            <p>Advt\n                            </p>\n\n                              \n                                                         \n                        <p>Scientists, policymakers, and public health officials across India have congratulated her on the achievement. Former CSIR director general Raghunath Mashelkar said, “Very proud moment for Indian science — and for us Indians.”Dr Soumya’s father, agricultural scientist <a href=\"/tag/m+s+swaminathan\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">M S Swaminathan</a>, was elected FRS in 1973, making them the first father-daughter FRS duo from India.                    </p><!-- Category Most Read Placement -->\n                                                                    \n                                                                \n                                <ul>\n                                    \n\n                                                                        <li><a href=\"/agency/87654367/TNN\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">TNN</a></li>\n                                </ul>\n                                <ul>\n                                    <!-- <li> Updated On 